reviews.review_text: My 62nd Show Really good first night of this Forum run. The boys are in fine form, especially Phil and Brent. Energy of the first set is great. Great song choices. Love seeing BIODTL. Blow Away is a winner.  I was lucky enough to see the last Help/Slip/Franklin’s prior to its reemergence a month earlier at Hampton Col. Very happy to see that back in the mix, though this version is a little subdued. Slipknot is pretty trippy & completely melts down, which is weird and cool. Franklin’s picks up nicely thanks in no small part to Brent. They do an Other One jam at the end of a solid He’s Gone. And once they get back to it after I Will Take You Home, it smokes (as usual). An excellent show. 4.5 stars rounded up for song choice.
